Influenza virus is the most important pathogen that causes acute lower respiratory infections (
 WHO, 2018b). The OST, a neuraminidase inhibitor, is the main anti-influenza used in clinics, but strains resistant to this molecule have been in clinical treatments reported worldwide, mandating the development of novel therapeutics (
 Dixit et al., 2013; 
 Lopes e Souza et al., 2015; 
 Souza et al., 2011).
